[announcer] <i>Oh, look out!
Franchitti's upside down.</i>


952
00:42:49.655 --> 00:42:51.282
<i>Wheldon is involved.</i>

953
00:42:51.783 --> 00:42:53.116
<i>Dixon is involved.</i>

954
00:42:53.117 --> 00:42:55.453
[ominous music playing]

955
00:42:58.956 --> 00:43:01.542
[Susie]
I'd seen him wreck before.


956
00:43:05.088 --> 00:43:07.590
But it definitely
felt different.


957
00:43:07.965 --> 00:43:09.466
[tires screeching]

958
00:43:09.467 --> 00:43:11.302
[crowd gasps]

959
00:43:12.637 --> 00:43:15.972
[Susie] This is the person
that I'm falling in love with


960
00:43:15.973 --> 00:43:18.683
and I want to have
a future with.


961
00:43:18.684 --> 00:43:21.562
That could completely be gone.

962
00:43:23.106 --> 00:43:24.774
I'm dying inside.

963
00:43:26.609 --> 00:43:28.152
[Chip] <i>Dan, do you copy?</i>

964
00:43:32.198 --> 00:43:34.492
He'd said something to me after.

965
00:43:35.409 --> 00:43:39.163
"You know, it's not always
great to date a driver,


966
00:43:39.831 --> 00:43:43.668
and I want to make sure that
you're gonna be okay with it."


967
00:43:45.336 --> 00:43:49.132
It's gonna sound really
selfish on his part,


968
00:43:49.799 --> 00:43:52.050
but I always knew that it was

969
00:43:52.051 --> 00:43:55.554
motor racing and then... me.

970
00:43:55.555 --> 00:43:57.598
[solemn music playing]

971
00:44:03.813 --> 00:44:05.565
[go-kart engines revving]

972
00:44:09.360 --> 00:44:12.155
[announcer] <i>Oh, massive impact
out of turn number 11.</i>


973
00:44:12.530 --> 00:44:15.158
<i>Big trouble for
Sebastian Wheldon.</i>


974
00:44:16.701 --> 00:44:18.285
<i>Right there in the middle
of the track,</i>


975
00:44:18.286 --> 00:44:21.080
<i>the karts were piled up
on top of each other.</i>


976
00:44:25.918 --> 00:44:27.712
[engine revving]

977
00:44:38.139 --> 00:44:40.349
- [tires screech]
- [go-kart thunks]


978
00:44:45.146 --> 00:44:46.730
[Sebastian] Help me!

979
00:44:46.731 --> 00:44:47.856
Somebody!

980
00:44:47.857 --> 00:44:49.317
Help!

981
00:44:53.237 --> 00:44:55.865
[go-kart crunching]

982
00:45:01.537 --> 00:45:04.373
- Help me. No, please...
- You can't. You can't.


983
00:45:05.416 --> 00:45:07.083
- [Sebastian] Can I get on?
- No.


984
00:45:07.084 --> 00:45:08.586
[Sebastian scoffs]

985
00:45:12.131 --> 00:45:13.883
[Sebastian whimpers]

986
00:45:14.842 --> 00:45:18.304
[Susie] Their safety is a big
part of what I think about.


987
00:45:18.763 --> 00:45:21.765
And as they get into it
deeper and deeper,


988
00:45:21.766 --> 00:45:23.141
the stakes get a lot higher,

989
00:45:23.142 --> 00:45:25.560
and this could all go
really wrong.


990
00:45:25.561 --> 00:45:27.772
[siren wailing]

991
00:45:30.358 --> 00:45:33.236
I could have waited
until they're older.


992
00:45:33.528 --> 00:45:35.446
But it's too late.
You can't.


993
00:45:37.198 --> 00:45:40.158
So when do they usually...
For these drivers,


994
00:45:40.159 --> 00:45:44.955
when do they move up to
kind of Indy 500 and Formula?


995
00:45:44.956 --> 00:45:46.289
After 16, 17 years?

996
00:45:46.290 --> 00:45:47.999
Eighteen? What's the cutoff?

997
00:45:48.000 --> 00:45:49.794
No. No, they, um...

998
00:45:50.628 --> 00:45:53.255
So in Junior Class,
they'll start testing,


999
00:45:53.256 --> 00:45:55.591
like, a Formula car
when they're 14.


1000
00:46:04.142 --> 00:46:05.809
[Sven] I'm nervous when
I think about Dan,


1001
00:46:05.810 --> 00:46:07.228
what happened to him.

1002
00:46:08.104 --> 00:46:09.271
So, you always hope and pray,

1003
00:46:09.272 --> 00:46:11.524
that will never happen
to the boys.


1004
00:46:14.110 --> 00:46:17.613
It's kind of sad to even
go back to that moment,


1005
00:46:17.989 --> 00:46:19.489
but I remember Susan and Dan,

1006
00:46:19.490 --> 00:46:22.368
they sang "Happy Birthday"
for me at 9:00 in the morning.


1007
00:46:23.369 --> 00:46:25.204
And I remember telling Dan...

1008
00:46:26.831 --> 00:46:28.207
[sniffles]

1009
00:46:29.083 --> 00:46:31.419
[somber music playing]

1010
00:46:36.340 --> 00:46:38.049
[softly] It's okay.

1011
00:46:38.050 --> 00:46:39.552
It's okay.

1012
00:46:39.886 --> 00:46:40.970
I know.

1013
00:46:41.512 --> 00:46:43.221
[Susie] <i>The dangers
of the sport,</i>


1014
00:46:43.222 --> 00:46:45.266
<i>it's the big elephant
in the room.</i>


1015
00:46:46.476 --> 00:46:48.603
<i>Dan and I never spoke about it.</i>

1016
00:46:49.771 --> 00:46:50.896
Hi.

1017
00:46:50.897 --> 00:46:52.815
My name is Susie Behm,

1018
00:46:53.316 --> 00:46:56.903
soon to be Susie Wheldon.

1019
00:46:58.696 --> 00:47:01.824
<i>I have never spoken about it
with other wives either.</i>


1020
00:47:03.534 --> 00:47:07.163
It's not often I cry, but I
really wanted to say to you,


1021
00:47:07.497 --> 00:47:10.123
that it makes me so proud and
happy to call you my wife.


1022
00:47:10.124 --> 00:47:12.125
You make me so very happy,

1023
00:47:12.126 --> 00:47:13.710
and I hope I do
the same for you.


1024
00:47:13.711 --> 00:47:14.796
So, thank you.

1025
00:47:15.838 --> 00:47:17.923
[Susie] It's just something
you do not talk about.


1026
00:47:17.924 --> 00:47:19.842
[camera shutter clicking]

1027
00:47:21.094 --> 00:47:22.594
And, of course,

1028
00:47:22.595 --> 00:47:24.554
the big joke in racing is, like,

1029
00:47:24.555 --> 00:47:26.264
once you get married,
you, like, slow down


1030
00:47:26.265 --> 00:47:27.516
and you're not as good.

1031
00:47:27.517 --> 00:47:29.560
So, I'm like, "Oh, my, God."
[chuckles]


1032
00:47:30.228 --> 00:47:32.145
[reporter] <i>IRL CEO Tony George</i>

1033
00:47:32.146 --> 00:47:34.606
<i>and Champ Car
World Series co-owner</i>


1034
00:47:34.607 --> 00:47:35.774
<i>Kevin Kalkhoven</i>

1035
00:47:35.775 --> 00:47:38.527
<i>shook hands to unify
the Indy Racing League.</i>


1036
00:47:38.528 --> 00:47:40.237
[Bryan] The IRL was formed

1037
00:47:40.238 --> 00:47:42.405
as an oval-only championship.

1038
00:47:42.406 --> 00:47:44.784
But as time went on,

1039
00:47:45.243 --> 00:47:46.535
the series started to evolve,

1040
00:47:46.536 --> 00:47:48.411
and it started moving towards

1041
00:47:48.412 --> 00:47:50.038
more road courses

1042
00:47:50.039 --> 00:47:51.331
and street courses.

1043
00:47:51.332 --> 00:47:52.874
And as they added more of those,

1044
00:47:52.875 --> 00:47:55.920
they became more important
to the overall championship.


1045
00:47:58.256 --> 00:48:00.048
[Scott] On ovals,
he was very good


1046
00:48:00.049 --> 00:48:02.592
at analyzing and understanding,

1047
00:48:02.593 --> 00:48:04.511
and his OCD
kicked into high gear.


1048
00:48:04.512 --> 00:48:06.805
He knew what he needed to do.
But with road courses,


1049
00:48:06.806 --> 00:48:09.851
there's a lot more variables,
different things going on.


1050
00:48:10.268 --> 00:48:13.104
The style of driving
that would then come in,


1051
00:48:13.396 --> 00:48:14.897
it didn't suit him.

1052
00:48:16.190 --> 00:48:17.817
[tires squealing]

1053
00:48:21.279 --> 00:48:22.779
It's a case of just
getting the car


1054
00:48:22.780 --> 00:48:25.282
to do what you want it to do
on the road courses,


1055
00:48:25.283 --> 00:48:26.825
and I haven't been able
to achieve that.


1056
00:48:26.826 --> 00:48:28.452
[announcer] <i>Look out.
Under heavy braking,</i>


1057
00:48:28.453 --> 00:48:29.786
<i>somebody's gotta go straight.</i>

1058
00:48:29.787 --> 00:48:32.456
<i>A right rear failure on
Dan Wheldon's car.</i>


1059
00:48:32.457 --> 00:48:36.001
At the same time, Scott
is absolutely smashing it.


1060
00:48:36.002 --> 00:48:37.670
He's winning everything.

1061
00:48:38.671 --> 00:48:40.380
[Chip] He won
the Indianapolis 500


1062
00:48:40.381 --> 00:48:42.300
and he won the championship.

1063
00:48:42.717 --> 00:48:44.676
And some of that was really due

1064
00:48:44.677 --> 00:48:46.386
to what he'd learned from Dan

1065
00:48:46.387 --> 00:48:49.265
the previous years of them
being teammates.


1066
00:48:49.932 --> 00:48:52.894
He opened the gate to a totally
different dimension for me.


1067
00:48:55.188 --> 00:48:58.273
[Dario] Dan's driving was
so much about confidence.


1068
00:48:58.274 --> 00:49:00.150
And, of course, the more
people talked about it,


1069
00:49:00.151 --> 00:49:02.028
the more it became mental.

1070
00:49:02.820 --> 00:49:04.654
[Dan] It's a sport I'm very
passionate about.


1071
00:49:04.655 --> 00:49:06.364
It's all I've grown up knowing.

1072
00:49:06.365 --> 00:49:08.200
I'd like to be remembered
as a winner,


1073
00:49:08.201 --> 00:49:12.163
and I want to be considered one
of the best drivers of all time.


1074
00:49:12.580 --> 00:49:14.122
It's what makes me tick.

1075
00:49:14.123 --> 00:49:16.541
My goals are to win,
and if I'm not achieving them,


1076
00:49:16.542 --> 00:49:19.002
I'm not a happy person
and I don't feel successful.


1077
00:49:19.003 --> 00:49:21.589
So, winning's all that matters.

1078
00:49:22.006 --> 00:49:23.424
It's all that counts.

1079
00:49:24.675 --> 00:49:28.011
[Chip] We put some pressure on
to make some changes


1080
00:49:28.012 --> 00:49:29.179
in the way he did things,

1081
00:49:29.180 --> 00:49:31.682
and he wasn't real accepting
of that,


1082
00:49:32.016 --> 00:49:34.226
and we started to drift apart.

1083
00:49:34.227 --> 00:49:36.770
[solemn music playing]

1084
00:49:36.771 --> 00:49:38.230
My contract is up.

1085
00:49:38.231 --> 00:49:40.024
I've been on Andretti forever.

1086
00:49:40.441 --> 00:49:44.195
Chip calls me, and he offers
me Dan's spot.


1087
00:49:45.196 --> 00:49:46.823
I'm very divided.

1088
00:49:47.406 --> 00:49:50.784
What am I gonna tell Dan?
But then you go, "Well,


1089
00:49:50.785 --> 00:49:53.663
he didn't tell me
when he left Andretti."


1090
00:49:54.747 --> 00:49:57.040
[announcer]
<i>Dan Wheldon in the ten.</i>


1091
00:49:57.041 --> 00:49:58.667
[Tony] We go to Kentucky

1092
00:49:58.668 --> 00:50:00.961
and we're racing
really hard together,


1093
00:50:00.962 --> 00:50:04.673
and he did something that
we do to other people,


1094
00:50:04.674 --> 00:50:06.716
but we never did to
each other, ever.


1095
00:50:06.717 --> 00:50:08.844
[announcer] <i>Wheldon takes
the air off of Tony.</i>


1096
00:50:08.845 --> 00:50:10.971
<i>That's a bit of a dirty play,
I'll tell you that.</i>


1097
00:50:10.972 --> 00:50:13.056
<i>That's not something that you
generally see between people</i>


1098
00:50:13.057 --> 00:50:15.600
<i>that know each other well
and used to be teammates.</i>


1099
00:50:15.601 --> 00:50:17.270
[Tony] After the race,

1100
00:50:17.645 --> 00:50:19.563
I go, "What was that?"

1101
00:50:19.564 --> 00:50:22.608
And he just told me, "Go f..."

1102
00:50:23.568 --> 00:50:24.944
and slammed the door on me.

1103
00:50:27.488 --> 00:50:29.198
We didn't speak for two years.

1104
00:50:29.699 --> 00:50:32.909
I decided at the last minute
to stay with Andretti.


1105
00:50:32.910 --> 00:50:36.914
Chip had to go back to his
fallback which was re-sign Dan.


1106
00:50:38.040 --> 00:50:39.958
[Chip] When it came
down to it, we said,


1107
00:50:39.959 --> 00:50:42.502
"Dan, we'd like to have you.
We wanna offer this seat."


1108
00:50:42.503 --> 00:50:44.045
- He said...
- "Oh, hey, Chip.


1109
00:50:44.046 --> 00:50:46.883
You got the wrong number.
Are you trying to reach Tony?


1110
00:50:47.425 --> 00:50:48.592
I'm the second choice now?

1111
00:50:48.593 --> 00:50:50.218
Then I've already moved on.

1112
00:50:50.219 --> 00:50:51.845
I'm going to find somebody else.

1113
00:50:51.846 --> 00:50:53.097
Sorry."

1114
00:50:55.016 --> 00:50:56.016
[chuckles]

1115
00:50:56.225 --> 00:50:59.227
He was a risk-taker,
and sometimes it paid off


1116
00:50:59.228 --> 00:51:00.855
and sometimes it didn't.

1117
00:51:01.773 --> 00:51:04.274
I'm the opposite.
I'm always second-guessing


1118
00:51:04.275 --> 00:51:05.859
and like, "Oh, my God,
is this right?


1119
00:51:05.860 --> 00:51:08.236
How is this gonna be
two years from now, ten years?"


1120
00:51:08.237 --> 00:51:11.073
I think that's one of the things
I fell in love with.


1121
00:51:11.783 --> 00:51:13.658
[Chip] When Dan left the team,

1122
00:51:13.659 --> 00:51:16.036
we offered the drive
to Dario Franchitti.


1123
00:51:16.037 --> 00:51:17.830
And I took over the 10 car.

1124
00:51:20.583 --> 00:51:22.794
I've made worse decisions.
[chuckles]


1125
00:51:23.211 --> 00:51:24.711
[crowd cheering]

1126
00:51:24.712 --> 00:51:28.799
[announcer] <i>Dario will win
his second Indianapolis 500</i>


1127
00:51:28.800 --> 00:51:31.803
<i>in the bright red Target car,
number 10.</i>


1128
00:51:32.428 --> 00:51:36.140
That... stung a little bit.

1129
00:51:39.143 --> 00:51:40.811
[announcer 1] <i>Tough one
