1133
00:51:49.779 --> 00:51:51.571
<i>lost a handful of spots.</i>

1134
00:51:51.572 --> 00:51:53.532
<i>Clearly not where
he was looking to be</i>


1135
00:51:53.533 --> 00:51:55.951
<i>or was expected to be.</i>

1136
00:51:55.952 --> 00:51:58.162
[somber music playing]

1137
00:51:59.580 --> 00:52:01.666
Do you want me to
get you some lunch?


1138
00:52:03.334 --> 00:52:04.752
What would you like?

1139
00:52:06.504 --> 00:52:08.088
- It's okay.
- Are you sure?


1140
00:52:08.089 --> 00:52:09.549
Yes, I'm sure.

1141
00:52:16.848 --> 00:52:18.723
How did the engine feel?
Like you had power?


1142
00:52:18.724 --> 00:52:20.183
Or was it just the chassis?

1143
00:52:20.184 --> 00:52:22.812
[Oliver speaks indistinctly]

1144
00:52:24.021 --> 00:52:25.021
Huh?

1145
00:52:25.022 --> 00:52:27.859
[indistinct chatter]

1146
00:52:31.446 --> 00:52:32.947
[child whimpers]

1147
00:52:42.039 --> 00:52:44.416
[Susie] One day, these boys
are gonna say to me,


1148
00:52:44.417 --> 00:52:46.710
"I wish our Dad was here
and not you.


1149
00:52:46.711 --> 00:52:48.044
My mom doesn't know anything,

1150
00:52:48.045 --> 00:52:49.963
and if my dad was here
it'd be so much better."


1151
00:52:49.964 --> 00:52:51.715
[announcer 1]
<i>Sebastian Wheldon,</i>


1152
00:52:51.716 --> 00:52:55.051
<i>only able move up
six spots to 23rd.</i>


1153
00:52:55.052 --> 00:52:57.221
[engines revving]

1154
00:52:58.055 --> 00:52:59.931
Your times are not bad
towards the end.


1155
00:52:59.932 --> 00:53:01.975
- I was looking at them.
- [clattering]


1156
00:53:01.976 --> 00:53:03.268
Are you okay?

1157
00:53:03.269 --> 00:53:04.644
Huh? No?

1158
00:53:04.645 --> 00:53:06.939
You don't need to be
throwing my phone around.


1159
00:53:12.195 --> 00:53:14.781
It's just like the dagger
to the heart.


1160
00:53:16.365 --> 00:53:19.576
But that's their own grief that
they're gonna have to learn


1161
00:53:19.577 --> 00:53:23.289
to process and navigate
and understand.


1162
00:53:26.667 --> 00:53:28.252
[Leo] <i>What I can say?</i>

1163
00:53:28.586 --> 00:53:30.545
You, Sebastian. 
Come on, buddy.

1164
00:53:30.546 --> 00:53:31.588
You're not thinking.

1165
00:53:31.589 --> 00:53:33.298
You're just driving.

1166
00:53:33.299 --> 00:53:34.758
You know Dallara?

1167
00:53:34.759 --> 00:53:37.053
Why he's sponsoring you?
No, you don't know.


1168
00:53:37.595 --> 00:53:39.347
We are a disaster.

1169
00:53:40.431 --> 00:53:42.766
So, what direction we wanna go?

1170
00:53:42.767 --> 00:53:45.602
If you wanna go forward,
be professional,


1171
00:53:45.603 --> 00:53:47.813
or just hanging around
with other guys?


1172
00:53:47.814 --> 00:53:50.942
[somber music continues]

1173
00:54:02.161 --> 00:54:04.663
I'm a little bit worried
because we're losing confidence.


1174
00:54:04.664 --> 00:54:07.332
I don't know...
I want to find why.


1175
00:54:07.333 --> 00:54:09.543
When you really kind of stop
and think about it,


1176
00:54:09.544 --> 00:54:12.796
it's like, you know, all these
kids are here with their dads.


1177
00:54:12.797 --> 00:54:17.217
You know? And it's like,
that has to be obvious,


1178
00:54:17.218 --> 00:54:19.803
and more obvious to them
as they're getting older.


1179
00:54:19.804 --> 00:54:22.139
I understand a little bit more,
yeah, yeah.


1180
00:54:22.140 --> 00:54:24.809
They're trying to process that
a little bit.


1181
00:54:28.271 --> 00:54:31.941
[Scott] <i>Dan had been humbled
through that couple of years.</i>


1182
00:54:32.859 --> 00:54:36.487
<i>His move to National Guard
Panther Racing, it was iffy.</i>


1183
00:54:36.946 --> 00:54:39.115
<i>That team had had its struggles.</i>

1184
00:54:39.824 --> 00:54:41.491
<i>But how you deal
with those moments</i>


