1424
01:05:26.888 --> 01:05:30.056
I just don't think we ever
didn't get better.


1425
01:05:30.057 --> 01:05:34.227
[announcer 2] <i>Pick up some pace,
about 228.7 for Dan Wheldon.</i>


1426
01:05:34.228 --> 01:05:36.021
It was like, okay.

1427
01:05:36.022 --> 01:05:37.564
Okay, this isn't too bad.

1428
01:05:37.565 --> 01:05:39.983
[solemn music playing]

1429
01:05:39.984 --> 01:05:41.526
[Dan] We've had a group that

1430
01:05:41.527 --> 01:05:44.154
has really brought the fun
back to racing for me.


1431
01:05:44.155 --> 01:05:46.282
[reporters laughing]

1432
01:05:46.866 --> 01:05:48.950
From my perspective,
I wanna come together


1433
01:05:48.951 --> 01:05:50.703
and just create a headline.

1434
01:05:54.582 --> 01:05:56.374
[Bryan] In the garage,

1435
01:05:56.375 --> 01:05:58.835
we had a little whiteboard
with a to-do list on it.


1436
01:05:58.836 --> 01:06:01.171
There's little boxes
and you'd check the box


1437
01:06:01.172 --> 01:06:02.924
after things were done.

1438
01:06:03.257 --> 01:06:04.633
The day before the race,

1439
01:06:04.634 --> 01:06:07.512
Dan looked at it and wrote
on the bottom,


1440
01:06:08.012 --> 01:06:09.680
"Win the Indy 500."

1441
01:06:10.014 --> 01:06:11.182
And, uh...

1442
01:06:13.351 --> 01:06:15.352
[voice breaks]
Now I'm gonna get emotional.


1443
01:06:15.353 --> 01:06:17.647
[soft music playing]

1444
01:06:18.773 --> 01:06:21.818
Oh, I kept it together
for so long. [clears throat]


1445
01:06:24.362 --> 01:06:25.737
[Tony] Before the 500,

1446
01:06:25.738 --> 01:06:29.617
the four of us went to
a very expensive steak house.


1447
01:06:30.827 --> 01:06:32.369
[Dario] There was a lot
of piss taking,


1448
01:06:32.370 --> 01:06:33.955
but then there was
a softer side.


1449
01:06:34.247 --> 01:06:36.957
It was more sort of, "Hey,
we've been through a lot."


1450
01:06:36.958 --> 01:06:39.292
And Dan was definitely more
thoughtful about


1451
01:06:39.293 --> 01:06:40.711
everything that happened.

1452
01:06:42.130 --> 01:06:47.050
It was a great moment where Dan
acknowledged what we...


1453
01:06:47.051 --> 01:06:48.468
That we had helped him.

1454
01:06:48.469 --> 01:06:51.848
Something he had never really
done in the past.


1455
01:06:52.974 --> 01:06:54.350
He said, "Hey, um...

1456
01:06:55.143 --> 01:06:57.352
thank you for everything
you guys have done for me.


1457
01:06:57.353 --> 01:06:58.938
I mean, I've learned a lot.

1458
01:06:59.397 --> 01:07:01.441
I'm a better person," and, uh...

1459
01:07:03.234 --> 01:07:05.236
that was our last dinner.

1460
01:07:07.738 --> 01:07:08.739
Sorry.

1461
01:07:09.657 --> 01:07:11.241
I promised I was not
gonna do that.


1462
01:07:11.242 --> 01:07:12.659
[exhales] Anyway...

1463
01:07:12.660 --> 01:07:15.997
I have a picture of us.
We took a picture.


1464
01:07:16.456 --> 01:07:17.747
I still have it.

1465
01:07:17.748 --> 01:07:19.374
We all do.
It's a bad picture


1466
01:07:19.375 --> 01:07:21.209
because we asked
somebody to take it.


1467
01:07:21.210 --> 01:07:23.044
It was on the inside
of a restaurant


1468
01:07:23.045 --> 01:07:24.881
with my phone with no flash.

1469
01:07:25.423 --> 01:07:27.717
[soft music continues]

1470
01:07:30.720 --> 01:07:32.679
[Dario] It was like, we've
been through a lot together


1471
01:07:32.680 --> 01:07:35.807
and it's cool that we're here
and we're still pals.


1472
01:07:35.808 --> 01:07:37.101
[sniffles]

1473
01:07:38.895 --> 01:07:40.480
[laughter]

1474
01:07:41.731 --> 01:07:44.483
- Oof! [groans]
- It's gonna be crazy today.


1475
01:07:44.484 --> 01:07:46.276
There's gonna be a lot
of people around


1476
01:07:46.277 --> 01:07:48.528
- and people that are gonna...
- 'Cause it's the Indy 500.


1477
01:07:48.529 --> 01:07:50.615
Yeah. But do you know why else?

1478
01:07:50.990 --> 01:07:53.242
It's been ten years
since Dad died?


1479
01:07:54.327 --> 01:07:56.536
You were just little.
You were a baby.


1480
01:07:56.537 --> 01:08:00.124
[soft, dramatic music playing]

1481
01:08:04.170 --> 01:08:07.923
[Susie] <i>In 2011, I was
at the hotel with the boys.</i>


1482
01:08:07.924 --> 01:08:10.634
I was just telling Oliver
that it's gonna be, like,


1483
01:08:10.635 --> 01:08:12.094
really busy this weekend,

1484
01:08:12.095 --> 01:08:14.429
and there's probably gonna
be cameras and stuff,


1485
01:08:14.430 --> 01:08:17.057
- 'cause it's a special year.
- Yeah.


1486
01:08:17.058 --> 01:08:20.728
[Susie] <i>We got a police
escort to the track.</i>


1487
01:08:21.813 --> 01:08:23.396
- I'm good. How are you?
- You are?


1488
01:08:23.397 --> 01:08:25.023
Yeah, not bad.
Hanging in there.


1489
01:08:25.024 --> 01:08:27.068
- Good luck today.
- Good to see you.


1490
01:08:28.194 --> 01:08:30.821
[Susie] <i>I wasn't there
on track with him</i>


1491
01:08:30.822 --> 01:08:32.740
<i>like I normally would be.</i>

1492
01:08:34.742 --> 01:08:36.119
[Dan] Where's Susie?

1493
01:08:36.494 --> 01:08:39.122
[Susie] <i>I was off with the boys
somewhere.</i>


1494
01:08:39.914 --> 01:08:43.835
<i>And I really did miss
having a role at the track.</i>


1495
01:08:44.460 --> 01:08:47.212
Now I'm here just to watch.

1496
01:08:47.213 --> 01:08:49.506
[announcer] <i>This is the 10th
anniversary of Dan Wheldon.</i>


1497
01:08:49.507 --> 01:08:50.924
<i>The Wheldon legacy carries on...</i>

1498
01:08:50.925 --> 01:08:52.135
Oh, hi!

1499
01:08:52.677 --> 01:08:54.678
[Susie] <i>There's a lot of
pomp and circumstance</i>


1500
01:08:54.679 --> 01:08:56.430
<i>with the Indy 500.</i>

1501
01:08:56.431 --> 01:08:57.806
[announcer]
<i>Susie Wheldon and the boys,</i>


1502
01:08:57.807 --> 01:09:00.518
<i>Sebastian, age 12,
Oliver, age 10.</i>


1503
01:09:01.018 --> 01:09:03.855
<i>They love this sport.
You can see it in their eyes.</i>


1504
01:09:04.355 --> 01:09:06.857
Dan died doing what he loved,

1505
01:09:06.858 --> 01:09:10.152
and now those boys are showing
that same passion


1506
01:09:10.153 --> 01:09:12.279
that Dan had for racing,

1507
01:09:12.280 --> 01:09:14.072
and Mom can feel that.

1508
01:09:14.073 --> 01:09:15.657
[dramatic music playing]

1509
01:09:15.658 --> 01:09:17.702
- [both singing]
- [rifles cocking]


1510
01:09:18.369 --> 01:09:20.163
[trumpet playing]

1511
01:09:20.872 --> 01:09:22.330
- [crowd cheering]
- [fireworks booming]


1512
01:09:22.331 --> 01:09:25.250
[arena announcer] <i>Ladies
and gentlemen, Dan Wheldon.</i>


1513
01:09:25.251 --> 01:09:26.835
[crowd cheering]

1514
01:09:26.836 --> 01:09:28.628
[Susie]
<i>He had something to prove.</i>


1515
01:09:28.629 --> 01:09:31.840
<i>Like, "I might not be here
full-time with you guys,</i>


1516
01:09:31.841 --> 01:09:35.052
<i>but by no means am I done."</i>

1517
01:09:37.138 --> 01:09:38.430
[jet engines roaring]

1518
01:09:38.431 --> 01:09:40.808
[crowd cheering]

1519
01:09:41.893 --> 01:09:43.810
[dramatic music playing]

1520
01:09:43.811 --> 01:09:47.063
[man on PA]
<i>Drivers, start your engines.</i>


1521
01:09:47.064 --> 01:09:49.232
It's gonna get loud
on the start.


1522
01:09:49.233 --> 01:09:50.693
I love it.

1523
01:09:51.277 --> 01:09:53.361
[man] <i>And the green flag waves.</i>

1524
01:09:53.362 --> 01:09:55.406
[engines roaring]

1525
01:09:58.159 --> 01:09:59.868
[Bryan] From the drop
of the green flag,


1526
01:09:59.869 --> 01:10:01.788
Dan was right in the mix.

1527
01:10:02.246 --> 01:10:03.247
He was locked in.

1528
01:10:06.918 --> 01:10:09.586
[announcer]
<i>It is Dixon, Servià, Tagliani.</i>


1529
01:10:09.587 --> 01:10:11.963
<i>Wheldon has got his foot
on the peg right now</i>


1530
01:10:11.964 --> 01:10:13.799
<i>trying to make up some time.</i>

1531
01:10:13.800 --> 01:10:16.969
You just watch him methodically
moving forward.


1532
01:10:18.137 --> 01:10:20.138
Which is the biggest thing
you want to do in these


1533
01:10:20.139 --> 01:10:21.599
500-mile races.

