01:41:14.660 --> 01:41:17.120
He was gonna be
driving for us again.


2112
01:41:17.121 --> 01:41:18.706
<i>♪ And I ♪</i>

2113
01:41:24.337 --> 01:41:26.214
<i>♪ Didn't ask you why... ♪</i>

2114
01:41:26.714 --> 01:41:27.964
[Scott] For Oliver
and Sebastian,


2115
01:41:27.965 --> 01:41:30.133
this is something that
they probably always


2116
01:41:30.134 --> 01:41:31.426
would've strived to do,

2117
01:41:31.427 --> 01:41:33.303
so I don't know
what's right or wrong.


2118
01:41:33.304 --> 01:41:35.680
<i>♪ What could I say... ♪</i>

2119
01:41:35.681 --> 01:41:39.101
[Scott] But I admire the courage
of Susie to support them


2120
01:41:39.102 --> 01:41:42.562
in something that has to be
extremely tough for her.


2121
01:41:42.563 --> 01:41:44.482
<i>♪ Far away... ♪</i>

2122
01:41:45.316 --> 01:41:47.651
[Dario] She knows Dan would've
wanted the boys to race.


2123
01:41:47.652 --> 01:41:50.529
You can't breed tame rabbits
from wild ones. [laughs]


2124
01:41:50.530 --> 01:41:53.241
[go-kart engines revving]

2125
01:41:56.994 --> 01:42:00.080
When they're in that kart,
they're closer to Dan


2126
01:42:00.081 --> 01:42:02.666
than they are at any other
point in their life.


2127
01:42:02.667 --> 01:42:04.877
<i>♪ And I just watch you... ♪</i>

2128
01:42:10.675 --> 01:42:12.008
Of course that's what it is.

2129
01:42:12.009 --> 01:42:14.303
[crowd cheering]

2130
01:42:15.263 --> 01:42:17.140
[Leo] Drive like a Wheldon.

2131
01:42:19.225 --> 01:42:21.561
<i>♪ How close am I ♪</i>

2132
01:42:26.399 --> 01:42:28.734
<i>♪ To losing you ♪</i>

2133
01:42:36.200 --> 01:42:38.368
[announcer] <i>Sebastian Wheldon
able to move up</i>


2134
01:42:38.369 --> 01:42:40.120
<i>six spots to fifth.</i>

2135
01:42:40.121 --> 01:42:41.538
[go-kart rattles]

2136
01:42:41.539 --> 01:42:44.750
<i>Wheldon the quickest driver
early on here.</i>


2137
01:42:46.711 --> 01:42:48.337
[music intensifies]

2138
01:43:16.616 --> 01:43:17.908
[inaudible]

2139
01:43:17.909 --> 01:43:20.077
["About Today"
continues playing]


2140
01:44:04.372 --> 01:44:05.831
[music softens]

2141
01:44:05.832 --> 01:44:06.957
[Susie] Check it out.

2142
01:44:06.958 --> 01:44:09.001
Your name's there
and everything.


2143
01:44:12.672 --> 01:44:14.214
[Oliver]
Bro, that suit fits you.


2144
01:44:14.215 --> 01:44:15.465
[laughs]

2145
01:44:15.466 --> 01:44:18.428
[race car engines revving]

2146
01:44:28.104 --> 01:44:29.813
[music fades]

2147
01:44:29.814 --> 01:44:31.314
[seat belt clicking]

2148
01:44:31.315 --> 01:44:33.525
[engines revving]

2149
01:44:33.526 --> 01:44:36.696
[engine roaring]

2150
01:44:46.789 --> 01:44:49.292
[dramatic string music playing]

2151
01:45:17.695 --> 01:45:21.031
2012 500 comes,
and everybody puts on those


2152
01:45:21.032 --> 01:45:23.951
dreadful white glasses
that Dan wore. [laughs]


2153
01:45:24.619 --> 01:45:27.371
[announcer] <i>Dario Franchitti
is gonna win the 500.</i>


2154
01:45:28.623 --> 01:45:30.665
[Scott] It was
a one, two, three finish.


2155
01:45:30.666 --> 01:45:33.294
Dario, myself, and TK.

2156
01:45:34.629 --> 01:45:36.505
[Tony] Dan's three best friends.

2157
01:45:36.506 --> 01:45:38.048
I couldn't believe it.

2158
01:45:38.049 --> 01:45:39.883
I'm like, wherever you are, man,

2159
01:45:39.884 --> 01:45:41.343
you have more powers
than we do now


2160
01:45:41.344 --> 01:45:44.638
because you see everything
wherever the hell you are.


2161
01:45:44.639 --> 01:45:46.098
But stop.

2162
01:45:46.099 --> 01:45:48.434
You can't, like... Really, stop.

2163
01:45:49.894 --> 01:45:52.312
You know when it says
like all the people


2164
01:45:52.313 --> 01:45:54.356
that were a part of the movie?
Am I going to be in that?


2165
01:45:54.357 --> 01:45:57.067
[producer] It's gonna say cast:
Sebastian Wheldon.


2166
01:45:57.068 --> 01:45:59.319
- Holy sh...
- [producer] Oliver Wheldon.


2167
01:45:59.320 --> 01:46:00.529
Susie Wheldon.

2168
01:46:00.530 --> 01:46:01.822
No, she's not in it.

2169
01:46:01.823 --> 01:46:03.240
Can we make bloopers in this?

2170
01:46:03.241 --> 01:46:05.952
- [producer] Yes.
- [Oliver] Let's go!


2171
01:46:07.912 --> 01:46:09.789
[indistinct chatter]

2172
01:46:10.915 --> 01:46:12.499
[Susie] Do not drop that.

