01:46:12.500 --> 01:46:13.959
[babbling]

2174
01:46:13.960 --> 01:46:15.962
Can I have headphones?

2175
01:46:17.922 --> 01:46:19.841
Honey, not up my nose.

2176
01:46:22.260 --> 01:46:25.762
How do you feel about, uh,
Dan Wheldon being your husband?


2177
01:46:25.763 --> 01:46:28.516
Well... [laughs]

2178
01:46:29.767 --> 01:46:31.352
Uh...

2179
01:46:31.978 --> 01:46:33.103
Speak to the camera.

2180
01:46:33.104 --> 01:46:34.646
What's Dan Wheldon
like to work with?


2181
01:46:34.647 --> 01:46:36.148
Speak right to the camera.

2182
01:46:36.149 --> 01:46:37.190
Well...

2183
01:46:37.191 --> 01:46:38.775
Could probably have
a one-on-one later


2184
01:46:38.776 --> 01:46:41.361
and I'll really tell you
but, um... it's very good.


2185
01:46:41.362 --> 01:46:44.532
[producer] Maybe don't block
her face there, Sebastian.


2186
01:46:45.241 --> 01:46:46.783
[Sebastian]
I love you to pieces.


2187
01:46:46.784 --> 01:46:49.536
- [Susie] I love you.
- [Sebastian] It's a wrap, guys.


2188
01:46:49.537 --> 01:46:51.914
[gentle music playing]

